'''Kamiyo Ame Candy''' is a [[:en:Yuzu|yuzu]]-flavored candy given out at {{ill|Kotohira Shrines|ja|金刀比羅神社}}<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Kamiyo Ame Candy |url=https://omotenashinippon.jp/selection/en/prize/2200-02-056/ |access-date=2023-09-17 |website=おもてなしセレクション（OMOTENASHI Selection） |language=en-US}}</ref>.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Kagawa {{!}} Pilgrimage to the Kotohira-gu Shrine {{!}} Authentic Japan: Setouchi |url=https://www.setouchi.travel/en/see-and-do/kotohira-gu-shrine/ |access-date=2023-09-17 |website=www.setouchi.travel |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-04-05 |title=Once-in-a-lifetime Konpira-san! Let's visit Kotohira Shrine |url=https://thegate12.com/article/205 |access-date=2023-09-17 |website=THE GATE}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Konpirasan – the famous Pilgrimage of Shikoku (Kagawa) |url=http://setouchifinder.com/en/detail/4242?pg=2 |access-date=2023-09-17 |website=Stouchi Finder |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Kotohira-gu |url=https://ikidane-nippon.com/en/spots/kotohira-gu |access-date=2023-09-17 |website=Ikidane Nippon |language=en-US}}</ref>

They are a kind of {{Ill|Tortoiseshell candy|ja|鼈甲飴}} that is eaten by breaking it apart with a small hammer.<ref name=":0" />

{{ill|Kotohira Shrines|ja|金刀比羅神社}} are [[shinto shrine]]s dedicated to [[Ōmononushi]]. Due to [[Shinbutsu-shūgō]] they often also worship {{ill|Konpira Gongen|simple}}

